            <h2>📜 Notable Ancestors & Their Legacy</h2>
            
            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h3>🏹 Th. Raja Goga Dev</h3>
                <p>The foundational figure of the Badgujar Rajputs, Th. Raja Goga Dev established the clan's dominance in central India. His fearless leadership and administrative acumen laid the groundwork for generations to come. He is revered as the patriarch whose valor set the standard for the Badgujar warriors.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h3>⚔️ Th. Khanderay Ji</h3>
                <p>A pivotal figure who expanded the clan's influence by moving from Banawad to Kotda in Kheechiwada. This strategic relocation strengthened the Badgujar political and economic power, establishing new territories that would serve as strongholds for centuries.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h3>🛡️ Th. Achal Singh Ji</h3>
                <p>His tenure marked the consolidation of Badgujar estates. Through strategic leadership and diplomatic skill, he navigated complex political landscapes, ensuring the clan's continued dominance in the Malwa region.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h3>🤝 Th. Rao Govardhan Singh Ji</h3>
                <p>During a tumultuous period marked by the decline of the Marathas and the rise of British influence, Th. Rao Govardhan Singh Ji skillfully maintained the family's status. His diplomatic acumen secured financial support from regional rulers including the Sindhia, Dewas, and Bhopal Darbar, ensuring the prosperity of the Dhabla Ghosi estate.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h3>👑 Th. Bhupendra Singh Ji</h3>
                <p>The ruler of Dhabla Ghosi during India's transition to independence, Th. Bhupendra Singh Ji played a crucial role in preserving the family's historical estates and cultural traditions. His leadership ensured the Badgujar Rajput legacy remained relevant and respected in modern India.</p>
            </div>

            <h2>🏛️ Contributions to History & Culture</h2>
            <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                <p>The Badgujar Rajputs' contributions extend far beyond their lineage:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>⚔️ Military Prowess:</strong> Known for their exceptional bravery and strategic brilliance, the Badgujars played vital roles in resisting foreign invasions and maintaining regional stability.</li>
                    <li><strong>📜 Administrative Excellence:</strong> Their governance promoted economic growth, social stability, and justice across their territories.</li>
                    <li><strong>🎨 Cultural Patronage:</strong> As great patrons of art, literature, and architecture, they built magnificent forts, palaces, and temples that stand as testaments to Rajputana grandeur.</li>
                    <li><strong>🙏 Social Contributions:</strong> Beyond military achievements, they promoted education, healthcare, and community development, ensuring the well-being of their subjects.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <p><strong>🙏 The Badgujar Rajput family lineage is a testament to honor, courage, and resilience.</strong> From Raja Goga Dev to the present generation, each ancestor contributed to the clan's prominence and the region's prosperity. Their legacy continues to inspire generations, preserving the rich cultural heritage of the Rajputana tradition.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px; text-align: center;"><em>🌹 "Veer Bhogya Vasundhara" - The brave inherit the earth 🌹</em></p>
